---
description: ActiveRecord models and database migrations
globs: app/models/**/*.rb,db/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

## Migrations

- Timestamped files in `db/migrate/`
- Run `bin/rails db:migrate`; use `bin/rails db:prepare` for fresh setups
- Some migrations are engine-generated (`.active_storage.rb`, `.solid_cache.rb`, etc.) — do not hand-edit those filenames

## Models

- Inherit `ApplicationRecord`
- UUIDs used for public IDs (`articles.uuid`, etc.) — prefer `param: :uuid` in routes
- Counter caches and `restrict_with_error` are common — preserve on delete semantics
- Annotated schema comments at top of model files (maintained by `annotaterb` in development)

## Domain notes

- Payments flow: `PreOrder` → `Order` → `Transfer` / `Payment` / revenue distribution jobs
- Crypto assets keyed by `asset_id` (Mixin Network UUID)
- User blocking: `blocked_at` on users; articles filter blocked authors in search

## Avoid

- Destructive data migrations without reversible `down` steps when feasible
- Changing revenue ratio columns without understanding `Orders::DistributeJob` impact
